{
  "texts": [
    "The observable to investigate is the branching fraction defined asB(µ -→ e -) = Γ(µ -→ e -) Γ capt,(70)which involves the muon capture rate Γ capt in the nucleus.",
    "The upper bound for B(µ → e) in 48 22 Ti established by the SINDRUM II experiment at PSI [65] isB(µ -→ e -) ≤ 4.3 × 10 -12 (at 90% C.L.).",
    "(71)For 48 22 Ti the values of the relevant parameters are Z ef f = 17.6 and F (q 2 ≃ -m 2 µ) ≃ 0.54 [66], with the muon capture rate Γ capt ≃ (2.590 ± 0.012) × 10 6 s -1 [67].",
    "This is the case considered in our analysis.",
    "An upper bound has been established by the SINDRUM II Collaboration also for the gold target: B(µ -Au → e -Au) ≤ 7 × 10 -13 [68]."
  ]
}